WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.200
There are some things we need to discuss.

00:03.320 --> 00:07.160
Our friend Jimmy McCavern
has asked for control of the racecourses

00:07.280 --> 00:08.480
north of Wincanton.

00:08.600 --> 00:10.040
I said yes.

00:10.160 --> 00:13.080
- In return for what?
- No return.

00:15.520 --> 00:16.640
None.

00:17.920 --> 00:21.600
I'm glad I didn't shoot you.

00:21.720 --> 00:23.800
It would have been a kindness.

00:25.120 --> 00:27.840
Now get out.

00:27.960 --> 00:29.400
THOMAS: This is a cheque guarantee.

00:29.520 --> 00:31.360
Signed by Mosley.

00:32.600 --> 00:35.680
On behalf of a man called Jimmy McCavern.

00:46.560 --> 00:48.480
THOMAS:
<i>The consequence of good intentions.</i>

00:49.560 --> 00:51.080
<i>My good intentions.</i>

00:53.200 --> 00:54.600
Push the button.

00:54.720 --> 00:56.920
Unlock the door and come home to me.

00:58.600 --> 01:00.160
(ENGINE STARTS)

01:01.920 --> 01:03.480
I have a job for you.

01:03.600 --> 01:05.600
(LAUGHS)

01:05.720 --> 01:07.480
I'll come for you...

01:07.600 --> 01:09.400
...after midnight on Wednesday.

01:09.520 --> 01:10.960
Barney Thomason...

01:12.240 --> 01:15.680
...is gonna kill Oswald Mosley.

01:15.800 --> 01:17.520
While he's on stage.

01:17.640 --> 01:19.160
While I'm stood next to him.

01:21.000 --> 01:23.840
And then I will take over
as leader of the party.

01:23.960 --> 01:27.320
THOMAS: <i>It's going to be a busy few weeks,
brother.</i>

01:40.120 --> 01:42.440
(DRINK POURS)

01:42.560 --> 01:44.280
(GLASS TINKLES)

01:47.800 --> 01:50.080
Mmm. (SNIFFS)

01:53.240 --> 01:54.920
(SNIFFS)

01:56.000 --> 01:58.120
You prefer Irish to Scotch?

01:59.840 --> 02:01.200
Yes, Mr Churchill.

02:05.440 --> 02:06.720
Irish over Scotch.

02:08.120 --> 02:10.280
Cigarettes over Havana cigars.

02:11.280 --> 02:13.520
And your mother
was probably born in a tent.

02:15.280 --> 02:16.760
Grandmother in a tent.

02:17.800 --> 02:19.720
My mother on a narrow boat.

02:20.760 --> 02:25.520
And always happy to give smart answers
to men born better than you.

02:26.600 --> 02:29.880
A man needs to prove he is better than me

02:30.000 --> 02:32.320
rather than show me his birth certificate.

02:32.440 --> 02:37.000
You see, I don't have one,
so they mean very little to me.

02:37.120 --> 02:40.080
You speak beautifully in the House.

02:40.200 --> 02:41.880
- Thank you.
- And believe

02:42.000 --> 02:43.840
not a word of what you are saying.

02:45.480 --> 02:49.920
Conviction introduces emotion,
which is the enemy of oratory.

02:50.040 --> 02:52.360
You read Greek literature.

02:52.480 --> 02:53.840
I have trouble sleeping.

02:58.080 --> 03:00.840
Is there a reason for your visit,
Mr Churchill?

03:01.840 --> 03:05.520
You are forming an alliance
with a fascist.

03:05.640 --> 03:10.840
So I made some enquiries
amongst the worst people in Whitehall,

03:10.960 --> 03:15.360
and I found out that you are not
forming an alliance with him at all.

03:16.600 --> 03:18.240
You are spying on him.

03:18.360 --> 03:20.160
Yes.

03:20.280 --> 03:21.280
Why?

03:24.640 --> 03:26.160
The honest answer is...

03:28.080 --> 03:29.360
...I'm no longer sure.

03:29.480 --> 03:32.760
Do you dig your own garden, Mr Shelby?

03:34.680 --> 03:36.000
I have a gardener.

03:37.080 --> 03:39.800
In fact, I have three gardeners.

03:41.240 --> 03:44.680
Three generations of men
with no ambition...

03:46.080 --> 03:48.120
...who are happier than I will ever be.

03:48.240 --> 03:52.080
Well, if you ask them, they will tell you

03:52.200 --> 03:54.720
that there are certain species of weed

03:54.840 --> 03:57.120
that no matter how much you tug at them,

03:57.240 --> 03:58.680
poison them,

03:58.800 --> 04:01.080
they continue to grow back.

04:01.200 --> 04:06.080
In the end, the only solution
is to plough up the topsoil,

04:06.200 --> 04:07.880
create a field of mud

04:08.000 --> 04:10.840
and blow up and burn
the exposed taproots.

04:12.320 --> 04:14.920
That's what you and I did in France.

04:15.040 --> 04:18.680
But when I hear that man Mosley speak,

04:18.800 --> 04:23.560
I see the green shoots of another war
growing up around his feet.

04:25.680 --> 04:29.000
And you see exactly the same thing I do.

04:29.120 --> 04:31.240
That's why you oppose him.

04:32.600 --> 04:33.840
Yeah.

04:34.880 --> 04:37.400
Your mystery solved.

04:39.440 --> 04:40.880
What is your strategy?

04:43.120 --> 04:45.160
I won't burden you with it.

04:45.280 --> 04:47.080
You're going to break the law.

04:48.480 --> 04:50.560
(SIGHS)

04:50.680 --> 04:51.720
I need to sleep.

04:53.280 --> 04:55.280
You said you don't sleep.

04:55.400 --> 04:57.280
I said I have trouble sleeping.

04:58.560 --> 04:59.560
As do I.

05:01.200 --> 05:02.240
As do I.

05:03.840 --> 05:05.240
Mr Shelby...

05:06.400 --> 05:10.280
...I have no doubt
that there was once a time in Flanders

05:10.400 --> 05:14.400
when you were under the ground
and I was above it,

05:14.520 --> 05:16.560
both working to the same end.

05:17.720 --> 05:23.040
We are in the same exact situation
here in Westminster.

05:25.240 --> 05:28.040
Do what you have to do, Mr Shelby.

05:32.280 --> 05:34.800
And if you need anything, call me.

05:39.760 --> 05:42.720
There are some times, some nights...

05:44.240 --> 05:48.000
...when I don't see the point
of carrying on with any of it.

05:48.120 --> 05:49.120
Oh.

05:50.560 --> 05:53.120
That old dance routine.

05:54.160 --> 05:55.800
I put out a cigar,

05:55.920 --> 05:59.080
and an hour later I want another.

06:00.440 --> 06:04.680
Sometimes, the bridge between hours
is as fragile as that.

06:06.080 --> 06:07.160
But use it anyway.

06:10.520 --> 06:12.320
A tent.

06:12.440 --> 06:13.720
Then a boat.

06:13.840 --> 06:15.360
Then a house.

06:15.480 --> 06:17.400
Now a mansion.

06:17.520 --> 06:19.520
That's something.

06:19.640 --> 06:20.680
Isn't it?

06:22.440 --> 06:25.000
Yeah, that is something.

06:28.560 --> 06:30.560
By the way...

06:31.720 --> 06:36.640
...was it you who killed
that Ulsterman intelligence officer?

06:36.760 --> 06:38.080
I forget his name.

06:38.200 --> 06:39.800
Major Campbell.

06:39.920 --> 06:42.520
Yes, Campbell.

06:42.640 --> 06:44.280
No.

06:44.400 --> 06:45.720
It was my aunt.

06:46.840 --> 06:49.360
I really must come up to Birmingham
some day

06:49.480 --> 06:51.280
and spend an evening with your family.

06:52.800 --> 06:54.480
They sound interesting.

06:54.600 --> 06:56.080
Yes.

06:56.200 --> 06:58.080
They'd like that.

07:09.080 --> 07:12.760
(SNORTING)

07:13.840 --> 07:16.600
I got to Harold French,
refereeing Liverpool. He just wants cash.

07:16.720 --> 07:18.800
Tom the tatter,
reffing Sheffield Wednesday, wants cash

07:18.920 --> 07:21.560
and a beating
for a bloke who's screwing his wife.

07:21.680 --> 07:23.960
The clap doctor said go easy
on the whiskey, yeah?

07:25.040 --> 07:26.240
Finn.

07:28.160 --> 07:29.320
You don't knock?

07:30.560 --> 07:32.080
No, Finn.

07:32.200 --> 07:34.320
I don't knock.

07:36.040 --> 07:37.200
Right.

07:38.880 --> 07:40.040
Hello, Billy.

07:41.120 --> 07:42.880
How are you, mate?

07:43.000 --> 07:44.400
Good, Mr Shelby.

07:44.520 --> 07:46.760
Yeah, you look good. (POURS DRINK)

07:46.880 --> 07:49.160
That's a nice suit.

07:49.280 --> 07:50.640
Thank you, Mr Shelby.

07:50.760 --> 07:52.240
FINN: He earned that suit.

07:52.360 --> 07:55.600
We made more on the matches
than we did on the races last Saturday.

07:55.720 --> 07:56.720
He's a good man.

07:56.840 --> 07:59.480
Yeah, I know that. Mm.

07:59.600 --> 08:01.600
You're coming up in the world, I like it.

08:03.800 --> 08:05.840
How's the missus, hmm?

08:06.920 --> 08:09.880
The old trouble and strife,
as the cockneys like to call it.

08:10.000 --> 08:11.160
She moved out.

08:11.280 --> 08:13.280
Oh, that's a shame.

08:13.400 --> 08:15.640
Mind if I join you, eh?

08:15.760 --> 08:20.040
Mind if I join the party?
Look at this, having some fun. Hmm?

08:22.880 --> 08:24.480
You're a good man, Billy.

08:26.440 --> 08:28.120
You're a good man, eh?

08:29.280 --> 08:32.080
You could sing like a bird in a cage.

08:32.200 --> 08:34.160
And what did we do, eh?

08:34.280 --> 08:39.440
We opened that cage,
and the real man flies out,

08:39.560 --> 08:42.000
reveals himself.

08:42.120 --> 08:44.440
The truth is young, Billy boy.

08:44.560 --> 08:46.000
Yeah.

08:46.120 --> 08:47.560
Here, look.

08:47.680 --> 08:50.040
What have we got here? Oh, look.

08:50.160 --> 08:52.560
Look at that, Billy boy, eh?

08:52.680 --> 08:54.240
Then there's some snow there, look.

08:54.360 --> 08:58.040
Oh, there's more.
Look, snowflakes, Billy.

08:58.160 --> 08:59.960
Now, I know you like that, hmm?

09:00.080 --> 09:01.320
Well, I do too.

09:01.440 --> 09:04.600
So, I'll tell you what, why don't we have
a little line together?

09:04.720 --> 09:06.960
Eh? Why don't we do
a little bit of snow together?

09:07.080 --> 09:08.080
(SNORTS)

09:08.200 --> 09:10.760
Oh, spilt it all down you an' all.

09:10.880 --> 09:13.120
It's the eyes. Sorry, mate.

09:13.240 --> 09:15.720
Hey, what can I do?
I'm messy, aren't I, Billy?

09:15.840 --> 09:17.200
I do apologise.

09:17.320 --> 09:19.360
And you. Hmm?

09:19.480 --> 09:20.560
Look at you.

09:20.680 --> 09:24.120
Sitting here with your mate, eh?
Your best mate.

09:24.240 --> 09:25.840
Well, while you're sitting here,

09:25.960 --> 09:28.240
talking about our business,

09:28.360 --> 09:31.280
drinking whiskey, smoking and sniffing...

09:31.400 --> 09:33.200
- Hmm?
- And working.

09:33.320 --> 09:36.720
You remember, you tell this man

09:36.840 --> 09:39.320
about our family business...

09:41.400 --> 09:43.160
...and it's his life you're risking.

09:43.280 --> 09:44.920
Cos people talk, Finn.

09:45.040 --> 09:47.560
We...we only ever talk about football
and women, Mr Shelby.

09:47.680 --> 09:50.160
(GLASS DROPS)

09:50.280 --> 09:51.400
Football and women,

09:51.520 --> 09:53.720
we only ever...we only ever talk
about football and women.

09:53.840 --> 09:55.560
- Oh, do you?
- Yeah.

09:55.680 --> 09:57.360
It's...

09:57.480 --> 09:58.680
Hmm.

10:00.400 --> 10:01.920
Yeah.

10:04.480 --> 10:05.800
Come on.

10:05.920 --> 10:07.360
Family meeting, let's go.

10:07.480 --> 10:08.880
(CHAIR SCRAPES)

10:15.960 --> 10:17.200
(DOOR OPENS)

10:18.800 --> 10:20.720
ARTHUR: You're not eating right.
You're not eating right.

10:20.840 --> 10:24.920
You're not getting the natural things
in you, boy, that's what it is, always.

10:31.640 --> 10:33.720
POLLY: You bearing up, Arthur?

10:33.840 --> 10:35.400
Bearing up for what?

10:36.680 --> 10:38.840
Bearing up to being free, Pol.

10:41.920 --> 10:43.680
ARTHUR: Another glass, eh?

10:43.800 --> 10:45.920
Another glass of so what.

10:51.600 --> 10:52.680
(DOOR OPENS)

10:52.800 --> 10:54.640
CURLY: Are you all right, Charlie?

10:56.520 --> 10:58.880
Mad bastard Barney kicked me
in the shin when I woke him up.

10:59.000 --> 11:00.320
Where is the mad bastard?

11:02.000 --> 11:04.480
He's tied to a lamp-post outside
with three Lee boys,

11:04.600 --> 11:06.600
shitting themselves.

11:08.640 --> 11:10.240
A drink.

11:16.520 --> 11:18.320
(CLEARS THROAT)

11:18.440 --> 11:19.760
THOMAS: First of all,

11:19.880 --> 11:24.840
an apology from Lizzie -
she can't be here.

11:24.960 --> 11:28.520
Charles has a violin concert.

11:29.880 --> 11:33.360
Also, a welcome to Mr Aberama Gold.

11:34.320 --> 11:38.960
He and Polly are to be married
in three weeks, with my blessing.

11:39.080 --> 11:43.000
From now on, Aberama will be welcome
at our meetings.

11:43.120 --> 11:46.040
First item of business, a bereavement.

11:47.520 --> 11:49.000
Colonel Ben Younger,

11:49.120 --> 11:52.560
who may perhaps have become
a member of this family,

11:52.680 --> 11:54.200
was taken from us,

11:54.320 --> 11:56.400
four days ago,

11:56.520 --> 11:58.200
by dark forces.

11:58.320 --> 12:00.640
We've made some investigations,

12:00.760 --> 12:02.720
and we think we know
who planted the bomb.

12:02.840 --> 12:05.480
In the meantime,
our thoughts are with Ada

12:05.600 --> 12:08.360
and the baby inside of her,

12:08.480 --> 12:11.880
who may one day sit at these meetings,

12:12.000 --> 12:15.560
but hopefully
under happier circumstances.

12:15.680 --> 12:18.120
Let's drink to happier circumstances.

12:18.240 --> 12:19.600
ARTHUR: Yeah.

12:21.040 --> 12:22.280
To Ada.

12:22.400 --> 12:25.800
- ALL: To Ada.
- Ada.

12:26.880 --> 12:29.400
(COUGHS) Item number two.

12:29.520 --> 12:30.960
An announcement,

12:31.080 --> 12:32.160
regarding Michael.

12:32.280 --> 12:35.240
(CLEARS THROAT) Before you go on, Tommy,

12:35.360 --> 12:39.200
there's something I'd like to say
to the whole family directly,

12:39.320 --> 12:42.320
regarding finances
and the future of this company.

12:42.440 --> 12:44.920
According to your own estimations,

12:45.040 --> 12:48.720
this new venture of the delivery
and shipment of opium

12:48.840 --> 12:51.760
will bring into the company
around £2 million per year.

12:51.880 --> 12:54.040
Therefore,

12:54.160 --> 12:56.560
due to the amounts involved,

12:56.680 --> 12:58.720
I think this company
should be restructured.

12:58.840 --> 13:02.640
Michael, I think this can wait
till outside the family meeting.

13:02.760 --> 13:03.960
Restructured in what way?

13:04.080 --> 13:06.040
GINA: Because of the amounts
of money involved,

13:06.160 --> 13:08.000
shipment and dispatch will become

13:08.120 --> 13:10.600
the primary source of income
to the company.

13:10.720 --> 13:13.240
It's simple mathematics.

13:13.360 --> 13:14.600
And with the help of my wife,

13:14.720 --> 13:17.560
I will organise an expansion into America,

13:17.680 --> 13:20.760
where the narcotics business
is just beginning to grow.

13:20.880 --> 13:23.640
So I have very good contacts in Detroit,

13:23.760 --> 13:27.400
New York, Boston,
who I've already spoken to about this.

13:27.520 --> 13:29.960
And Gina has family who are
very experienced in this kind of business.

13:31.760 --> 13:34.440
According to the conversations
I've had with them,

13:34.560 --> 13:35.920
with a regular supply

13:36.040 --> 13:37.720
of pure opium from China,

13:37.840 --> 13:40.120
within a short space of time,

13:40.240 --> 13:46.000
the American narcotics business
will bring in $20 million per annum.

13:46.120 --> 13:52.160
Enough money for you to all enjoy
an easing of the burden you all now feel.

13:53.480 --> 13:58.200
See, I know that the scars
and the wounds,

13:58.320 --> 13:59.880
they're on the inside,

14:00.000 --> 14:01.520
not on the outside.

14:01.640 --> 14:03.840
And as a member of the new generation,

14:03.960 --> 14:07.760
I'm able to take that great burden
off your weary shoulders.

14:09.280 --> 14:11.400
A new decade is coming.

14:11.520 --> 14:14.600
There'll be new opportunities
in new territories.

14:14.720 --> 14:16.320
More money than we've ever had before.

14:17.920 --> 14:19.680
Tommy,

14:19.800 --> 14:23.040
you can still do the good work
that deep down you want to do.

14:25.000 --> 14:29.280
Mum, you can get married
and live in that big house.

14:29.400 --> 14:31.760
Arthur, you can be the man
that Linda wants you to be.

14:31.880 --> 14:33.440
Fuck Linda.

14:36.440 --> 14:37.440
Finn.

14:39.080 --> 14:40.080
You've proved yourself.

14:42.400 --> 14:44.040
You're part of the new generation.

14:45.880 --> 14:47.920
You could come to New York with me.

14:52.400 --> 14:54.280
Here is my proposal.

14:55.920 --> 14:57.960
A full restructuring of the company.

14:58.080 --> 15:01.160
I will be managing director.

15:01.280 --> 15:03.440
And you can be non executive chairman.

15:03.560 --> 15:06.560
But under an assumed name,
to protect your reputation.

15:07.640 --> 15:09.200
I've found the name of a dead man.

15:09.320 --> 15:12.400
You will be registered as Mr Jones.

15:13.960 --> 15:17.760
You will each receive a percentage
of the profits as an annuity,

15:17.880 --> 15:23.440
and you will no longer have to engage
in any of the associated activities.

15:27.960 --> 15:30.200
Take a look at the future, Tommy.

15:31.800 --> 15:33.440
At least read it with an open mind.

15:41.720 --> 15:43.000
It's cold in here, Michael.

15:43.120 --> 15:44.480
(LAUGHTER)

15:44.600 --> 15:46.840
Tommy, the Americans want to deal with me.

15:46.960 --> 15:48.320
Item number three.

15:48.440 --> 15:50.720
GINA: Tell him the truth.

15:50.840 --> 15:51.880
Go on.

15:52.920 --> 15:54.800
He can take it.

16:00.560 --> 16:02.720
Tell me the truth, Michael.

16:05.280 --> 16:09.360
The Americans don't want to deal with
an old-fashioned backstreet razor gang.

16:09.480 --> 16:11.440
Those days are done.

16:15.640 --> 16:18.240
Tommy. He's bitten through
the fucking rope.

16:18.360 --> 16:19.560
They've got him cornered,
but they need help.

16:19.680 --> 16:21.560
Go and get him!

16:24.680 --> 16:26.560
Fuck the Americans.

16:37.120 --> 16:39.440
I'm doing this for you, Tommy.

16:41.040 --> 16:42.520
It's time.

16:44.320 --> 16:45.440
And you know it.

16:46.800 --> 16:48.440
Tommy, Mum's leaving...

16:49.680 --> 16:52.880
...John's dead, Arthur needs help,

16:53.000 --> 16:56.560
Ada's man was killed in your own back yard
because you fucked up.

16:58.360 --> 17:01.760
Go on, Tom. Go on, cut me.

17:02.880 --> 17:04.360
Like the good old days.

17:05.440 --> 17:06.440
Or...

17:07.560 --> 17:09.840
...see this for what it is.

17:11.720 --> 17:13.240
A natural succession...

17:14.280 --> 17:15.960
...that someday must happen.

17:21.640 --> 17:24.120
I gave you an opportunity, Michael.
You betrayed me.

17:25.360 --> 17:26.800
Don't be here when I get back.

17:26.920 --> 17:27.920
You. (CLICKS FINGERS)

17:29.320 --> 17:30.720
You can tell your family...

17:30.840 --> 17:32.800
Let me guess.

17:32.920 --> 17:34.560
Don't fuck with the Peaky Blinders.

17:37.720 --> 17:39.120
Right?

18:08.680 --> 18:10.800
- Well...
- (DOOR CLOSES)

18:10.920 --> 18:13.120
...guess we're gonna be forced
to take the second option.

18:17.880 --> 18:19.920
They're not fucking voices!

18:20.040 --> 18:23.160
Whoa! Whoa! Calm down.

18:23.280 --> 18:26.480
- Put the gun down.
- They're not fucking voices!

18:26.600 --> 18:28.000
Barney!

18:29.080 --> 18:30.240
Barney!

18:32.000 --> 18:34.360
Put down the gun. At ease.

18:35.720 --> 18:36.840
Finn.

18:39.200 --> 18:40.960
At ease, soldier. At ease.

18:41.080 --> 18:43.000
Look at me. You're on our side.

18:43.120 --> 18:45.040
You're at home.

18:45.160 --> 18:46.360
You're at home.

18:46.480 --> 18:48.720
Yeah? Yeah.

18:48.840 --> 18:51.680
Here. Take this, Barney. Jeremiah?

18:51.800 --> 18:53.640
Yeah.

18:53.760 --> 18:56.320
Take him to Charlie's yard
before he falls over.

18:56.440 --> 18:57.600
The devil will now be an angel.

18:57.720 --> 18:59.720
Isiah, Curly, you go with him.

18:59.840 --> 19:00.920
Come, brother.

19:01.040 --> 19:02.640
Let me give you the good news.

19:02.760 --> 19:04.040
Jesus loves you.

19:05.120 --> 19:06.480
So, where the fuck is he?

19:06.600 --> 19:07.680
THOMAS: All right, boys.

19:07.800 --> 19:12.760
A subsidiary meeting of the generation
that actually do the work.

19:27.000 --> 19:29.080
ARTHUR: Right.

19:29.200 --> 19:30.720
Let's have the good stuff.

19:30.840 --> 19:33.000
None of that shit ponces' drink.

19:33.120 --> 19:35.080
Here we go, look.

19:35.200 --> 19:37.960
All right, so item number three.

19:38.080 --> 19:39.920
An introduction.

19:40.040 --> 19:44.160
Except now you've already met the man
I was going to introduce.

19:44.280 --> 19:46.120
In France, he was a comrade.

19:46.240 --> 19:47.560
What the fuck is he now, Tom?

19:47.680 --> 19:50.120
He's a man we can use, Johnny.

19:50.240 --> 19:52.960
For what? Put him in a ring with a bear
and take bets on the outcome?

19:53.080 --> 19:56.040
I tell you, I wouldn't put much money
on the fucking bear.

19:57.720 --> 19:59.720
Aberama,

19:59.840 --> 20:03.760
that man is a trained Royal Marine sniper.

20:03.880 --> 20:05.920
Furthermore, he has a criminal profile

20:06.040 --> 20:09.280
which will make his actions explicable
to the police.

20:09.400 --> 20:11.200
What actions?

20:11.320 --> 20:12.760
A killing.

20:13.960 --> 20:16.040
ABERAMA: And since when
did you worry about the police?

20:18.560 --> 20:19.680
Barney Thomason...

20:21.080 --> 20:22.840
...is gonna kill an MP.

20:22.960 --> 20:25.800
Possibly the future prime minister
of Great Britain.

20:25.920 --> 20:28.240
What the fuck, Tom?

20:31.760 --> 20:33.520
(COUGHS)

20:33.640 --> 20:35.560
After the killing,

20:35.680 --> 20:38.200
there will be an investigation
by Special Branch

20:38.320 --> 20:39.480
and Intelligence forces.

20:41.160 --> 20:45.400
There will be a lot of powerful people
as angry as fucking hornets.

20:45.520 --> 20:48.160
We need there to be no connection to us.

20:48.280 --> 20:50.560
Barney Thomason is registered
as criminally insane.

20:50.680 --> 20:53.080
He broke out. He's an old soldier.

20:53.200 --> 20:55.040
He has known grievances.

20:55.160 --> 20:59.120
No-one will question
that the assassination was carried out

20:59.240 --> 21:01.600
by a single gunman acting alone.

21:01.720 --> 21:04.920
And you'd sacrifice an old comrade?

21:05.040 --> 21:07.280
If they catch him,

21:07.400 --> 21:10.680
they won't hang him
on grounds of insanity,

21:10.800 --> 21:13.440
just send him back to where I found him.

21:13.560 --> 21:15.240
He'll have had a very eventful holiday

21:15.360 --> 21:17.720
that he'll probably believe
never really happened.

21:17.840 --> 21:19.800
And where will this killing take place?

21:24.680 --> 21:25.680
ARTHUR: There you go.

21:33.280 --> 21:34.360
He'll be on stage.

21:34.480 --> 21:36.640
With lots...

21:37.680 --> 21:39.000
...of witnesses.

21:39.120 --> 21:41.200
During the rally,

21:41.320 --> 21:44.000
there will be
an anti-fascist demonstration.

21:44.120 --> 21:47.040
Amidst the confusion,
a shot will be fired.

21:47.160 --> 21:48.840
And we're organising this demonstration?

21:48.960 --> 21:50.080
Yeah.

21:50.200 --> 21:51.920
Where will you be, Tom?

21:55.280 --> 21:57.440
I'll be down on one knee,
cradling his head...

21:58.600 --> 22:00.000
...while the life drains from him.

22:01.720 --> 22:03.120
Then I'll make a speech...

22:04.320 --> 22:06.800
...saying how the cause he died for
must continue...

22:08.600 --> 22:10.080
...continue safe in my hands.

22:11.320 --> 22:12.440
ABERAMA: Holy fuck.

22:13.760 --> 22:15.120
Tommy...

22:16.520 --> 22:18.280
...does your ambition have no limits?

22:21.560 --> 22:24.400
Jimmy McCavern will be running security
at this event.

22:25.680 --> 22:27.160
He'll probably be in the wings.

22:28.400 --> 22:30.960
You can take his life
whichever manner you choose.

22:36.040 --> 22:37.960
What do you want us to do, Tom?

22:38.080 --> 22:40.080
You and Arthur
and a couple of the Lee boys,

22:40.200 --> 22:42.760
you'll be in charge
of getting Barney into position.

22:42.880 --> 22:45.120
He'll be up in the lighting gantry.

22:45.240 --> 22:46.720
We'll need chains and a twitch, Tom.

22:46.840 --> 22:48.840
No. I will medicate him.

22:48.960 --> 22:52.440
So he's gonna be cross-eyed
when he takes the shot?

22:52.560 --> 22:55.800
In France, he never missed...

22:56.840 --> 22:58.440
...no matter what they gave him.

22:59.720 --> 23:02.200
He'll have had plenty of target practice.

23:02.320 --> 23:04.040
Before he takes the shot,

23:04.160 --> 23:08.200
Arthur here will give him some cocaine
to sharpen him up.

23:08.320 --> 23:09.920
So just...

23:10.040 --> 23:11.720
You're gonna be up on the stage

23:11.840 --> 23:14.960
while this criminally insane gunman
filled with cocaine

23:15.080 --> 23:18.360
takes aim at a man
just a yard away from you?

23:20.440 --> 23:22.360
Welcome to the family, Aberama.

23:22.480 --> 23:25.800
What about me, Thomas?
The man with the broken fucking leg.

23:28.560 --> 23:29.920
After the killing,

23:30.040 --> 23:33.440
every copper in Birmingham
will be sent to Bingley Hall.

23:33.560 --> 23:35.720
Use that opportunity

23:35.840 --> 23:39.160
to get that boat full of opium
up to St our bridge locks.

23:39.280 --> 23:44.480
There, you'll be met
by some Chinese gentlemen.

23:44.600 --> 23:46.480
They will have two suitcases full of cash.

23:47.920 --> 23:49.720
£250,000.

23:52.200 --> 23:56.360
Every man in this room
will receive $30,000 in cash,

23:56.480 --> 23:58.360
in recognition of extra services.

23:58.480 --> 24:01.800
Holy Mary, Mother of God, Tom!

24:01.920 --> 24:03.080
(LAUGHS)

24:03.200 --> 24:07.160
THOMAS: Anyone who wants to leave,
leave now.

24:08.440 --> 24:11.680
Anyone who is tired
of this old-fashioned,

24:11.800 --> 24:15.760
backstreet fucking razor gang can leave.

24:15.880 --> 24:19.520
Anyone who's tired can fucking stop.

24:23.640 --> 24:24.760
Good.

24:26.120 --> 24:29.640
Charlie, go to the yard and light a fire.

24:29.760 --> 24:31.840
Johnny, bring the van round.

24:31.960 --> 24:34.960
What's the fire for, Tom?

24:36.720 --> 24:38.720
There is an item number four.

24:38.840 --> 24:41.400
(LAUGHTER)

25:00.200 --> 25:01.360
It's time.

25:15.760 --> 25:17.480
(DOOR IS UNLOCKED)

25:22.160 --> 25:23.480
(DOOR SHUTS)

25:23.600 --> 25:25.360
(CHEERFUL HUMMING)

25:28.440 --> 25:30.120
Jeez, Mr Shelby.

25:30.240 --> 25:33.000
If I'd have known, I'd have come in early
and served you drinks, huh?

25:37.200 --> 25:38.640
Here, Micky.

25:41.600 --> 25:42.680
Sit down there.

26:02.000 --> 26:03.440
So I'll have a drink, will I?

26:07.640 --> 26:09.160
Here you go, have a drink.

26:16.760 --> 26:18.760
A few days ago, I went to London, Micky.

26:22.240 --> 26:23.440
To collect some cargo.

26:26.840 --> 26:28.760
I was met by the Titanic boys.

26:31.120 --> 26:32.960
They knew I was coming.

26:35.120 --> 26:38.920
Yeah. When, where, what time.

26:39.040 --> 26:40.160
They even knew...

26:41.680 --> 26:42.760
...the cargo I was picking up.

26:42.880 --> 26:44.080
Jesus.

26:44.200 --> 26:46.120
Four days ago, Micky...

26:47.120 --> 26:48.520
...a soldier was killed...

26:49.560 --> 26:50.920
...outside my office...

26:52.200 --> 26:53.280
...by a bomb.

26:53.400 --> 26:57.040
Yeah, erm, the papers said that was IRA.

26:57.160 --> 26:58.320
No, it wasn't the IRA, Micky.

26:58.440 --> 27:01.240
No. It weren't the IRA.

27:05.000 --> 27:11.280
I spoke to the girls who work
at the Digbeth telephone exchange.

27:11.400 --> 27:12.520
They're friends of mine.

27:15.520 --> 27:20.600
I asked them what calls were made
around the time of the explosion.

27:22.800 --> 27:24.000
They told me that...

27:26.200 --> 27:30.240
...30 minutes before the explosion
a call was made to a man in Sparkhill

27:30.360 --> 27:33.880
who has connections
to the Ulster Volunteer Force.

27:34.000 --> 27:36.360
He now offers his services for cash.

27:36.480 --> 27:38.720
(ARTHUR TAPS GLASS)

27:42.400 --> 27:44.280
Paddy Rose.

27:48.320 --> 27:50.640
Yeah, me and my brother,
we spoke to Paddy.

27:51.920 --> 27:53.080
At length.

27:54.240 --> 27:56.960
He told us it was him
that planted the bomb.

27:59.280 --> 28:00.320
Yeah, we spoke to him.

28:05.120 --> 28:07.000
We killed him, Micky.

28:08.960 --> 28:10.400
Paddy Rose is dead.

28:10.520 --> 28:12.640
We weighed him down,

28:12.760 --> 28:14.760
we sunk him...

28:14.880 --> 28:17.040
...to the bottom of the Grand Union Canal.

28:22.600 --> 28:24.760
The girls at the exchange
gave me the number

28:24.880 --> 28:27.040
of the man that called, Micky,
before the explosion.

28:27.160 --> 28:28.440
That was your number.

28:30.640 --> 28:33.520
Micky, it was you who called him.

28:34.920 --> 28:35.920
You tipped him off.

28:38.640 --> 28:39.760
You were told to call him

28:39.880 --> 28:42.320
if a black man of a certain description
ever came to Small Heath.

28:50.040 --> 28:53.640
We know you've...you've been giving
the Titanic boys information as well.

28:55.200 --> 28:56.200
We know that.

28:57.480 --> 28:59.000
Yeah.

28:59.120 --> 29:02.080
You've been working behind the bar, hmm?

29:02.200 --> 29:06.680
Seeing what goes on, listening,
taking notes,

29:06.800 --> 29:10.560
and selling your stories
to the highest bidder. Hmm?

29:14.320 --> 29:16.240
Yeah.

29:16.360 --> 29:17.320
Come on.

29:17.440 --> 29:18.800
(WHIMPERS)

29:20.200 --> 29:21.280
Come on, man.

29:22.800 --> 29:24.200
(SOBS)

29:30.800 --> 29:33.520
Oh, Jesus. Oh, Jesus.

29:44.920 --> 29:46.360
I'm sorry, Mr Shelby.

29:53.360 --> 29:55.640
Don't look at Tommy.

30:01.200 --> 30:03.760
The ceiling would be cheaper, brother.

30:03.880 --> 30:05.120
Micky!

30:18.160 --> 30:19.800
Fucking hell, Arthur.

30:19.920 --> 30:21.160
Eh?

30:21.280 --> 30:23.280
Shaking like the hand of a normal man.

30:31.000 --> 30:33.280
What about item five, Tom?

30:33.400 --> 30:34.440
Huh?

30:36.280 --> 30:39.480
There is an item five, right, Tommy?

30:40.680 --> 30:42.600
(SOBS) I'm fucking sinking here, man.

30:46.760 --> 30:48.240
I'm fucking sinking, Tom.

30:49.800 --> 30:51.840
You...you...you said there's an item five.

30:51.960 --> 30:53.560
Say it, Tommy.

30:53.680 --> 30:57.600
Item five could start now, Tommy.

30:57.720 --> 31:01.000
It could start this year, a new decade.

31:02.200 --> 31:03.640
M-M-Michael...

31:03.760 --> 31:06.160
Michael could be right -
we could go, Tommy.

31:06.280 --> 31:08.000
We could go.

31:08.120 --> 31:10.080
We could fucking leave this place.

31:10.200 --> 31:11.920
We could leave it to the kids.

31:12.040 --> 31:14.480
Michael's... He might be right.

31:14.600 --> 31:16.520
- He might be fucking right.
- Arthur!

31:16.640 --> 31:20.560
(SHOUTS) There is no item number five!

31:33.280 --> 31:35.400
Go and check
that Polly is still on our side.

31:36.680 --> 31:38.240
I have to go to Margate.

31:38.360 --> 31:39.640
All right, Tom.

31:42.600 --> 31:43.880
All right, brother!

31:49.640 --> 31:52.880
Oh, God. Jesus Christ.

31:53.280 --> 31:55.240
(MUSIC PLAYS)

32:11.960 --> 32:13.400
ALFIE: You out there, Tommy?

32:15.360 --> 32:17.440
Yeah. I'm here.

32:17.560 --> 32:22.600
I was just having some oil rubbed
into the bits that really hurt, mate.

32:22.720 --> 32:25.800
What do you think of that view, eh?

32:27.320 --> 32:29.320
It's Margate. What can you do?

32:32.160 --> 32:33.800
- (RECORD SCRATCHES)
- (MUSIC STOPS)

32:33.920 --> 32:35.160
I'll tell you something, Tommy, right?

32:35.280 --> 32:38.560
I sit all day every day in that chair,

32:38.680 --> 32:42.520
on that balcony,
contemplating the fact, right,

32:42.640 --> 32:45.920
that life is so much easier to deal with
when you are dead!

32:49.800 --> 32:52.720
- Hello, Alfie.
- Yeah.

32:52.840 --> 32:54.840
Did you...did you look
through the binoculars?

32:54.960 --> 32:56.040
Yeah.

32:56.160 --> 32:58.240
I watch ships. No two are the same.

32:58.360 --> 33:00.200
Yeah.

33:00.320 --> 33:03.760
That is how God sees us both, in his eyes.

33:03.880 --> 33:05.240
God, eh?

33:05.360 --> 33:06.840
Yeah, sort of. I mean, you know.

33:06.960 --> 33:09.760
Someone's responsible
for all this fucking mess.

33:11.320 --> 33:12.280
Now...

33:12.400 --> 33:15.200
How soon did you know
that I was not dead?

33:15.320 --> 33:16.840
You wrote me a letter, Alfie.

33:16.960 --> 33:18.160
Did I?

33:18.280 --> 33:20.040
Yeah, you asked about your dog.

33:21.080 --> 33:23.720
They gave me a lot of drugs at first.

33:23.840 --> 33:26.400
Hmm. Yeah, all right.

33:26.520 --> 33:28.160
I was lying out there,

33:28.280 --> 33:31.200
and the tide had come in,
and it woke me up.

33:32.320 --> 33:35.000
I remember looking around
and thinking, you know...

33:36.320 --> 33:37.400
..."Fuck...

33:38.600 --> 33:40.400
"...if this is hell...

33:41.600 --> 33:43.480
"...it looks a lot like Margate."

33:43.600 --> 33:46.600
Maybe that's just what hell looks like,
eh?

33:46.720 --> 33:50.520
No, no, not according
to this holy book right here, yeah?

33:50.640 --> 33:53.760
It gives a very, very vivid description.

33:53.880 --> 33:55.680
You and I are both fucked, mate.

33:59.560 --> 34:01.400
Do you read the papers, Alfie?

34:01.520 --> 34:03.360
No, don't be silly.

34:03.480 --> 34:04.600
(GUN COCKS)

34:04.720 --> 34:05.840
But you've heard.

34:05.960 --> 34:07.720
What, fascism, yeah?

34:10.640 --> 34:11.760
Three,

34:11.880 --> 34:13.480
two,

34:13.600 --> 34:15.320
one,

34:15.440 --> 34:16.920
bang.

34:17.040 --> 34:18.120
No?

34:20.360 --> 34:21.760
Fine.

34:23.040 --> 34:25.480
Good Lord, your fucking condition
has got worse, mate.

34:25.600 --> 34:28.360
- (THOMAS COUGHS)
- Mine, on the other hand,

34:28.480 --> 34:30.120
I've been living the dream.

34:30.240 --> 34:33.240
Sometimes, I will shoot
at the side of a ship.

34:33.360 --> 34:36.120
And sometimes I'll sit here,
I may shoot at the old seagull.

34:36.240 --> 34:37.440
Alfie...

34:40.560 --> 34:42.720
...I'm gonna shoot Oswald Mosley.

34:42.840 --> 34:44.080
Right, well...

34:45.240 --> 34:48.240
...I hope you do a better job on him
than the one you done on me, yeah?

34:49.680 --> 34:54.360
I mean, what...what were you thinking?
Was your mind somewhere else, Tommy?

34:56.080 --> 34:57.800
Yes, it was, actually.

34:57.920 --> 35:01.240
- Yeah, all right.
- (SHIP HORN BLARES)

35:01.360 --> 35:03.000
Oh, look.

35:04.080 --> 35:05.200
A ship.

35:12.600 --> 35:14.160
Why do you want to shoot him?

35:15.160 --> 35:18.200
I need to organise a riot, Alfie.

35:18.320 --> 35:19.280
Right.

35:19.400 --> 35:23.280
And I hear you still have some...standing

35:23.400 --> 35:25.720
in the Jewish community.

35:25.840 --> 35:29.200
Let me be clear, right?

35:29.320 --> 35:31.680
Since my resurrection,

35:31.800 --> 35:35.600
I am considered to be a god, all right?

35:35.720 --> 35:39.960
In the Holy Land,
someone has made an image of me

35:40.080 --> 35:43.440
out of rock embedded in the sand,
so I'm told,

35:43.560 --> 35:47.080
and I am planning to make
a pilgrimage to stand in my own shadow.

35:52.600 --> 35:56.400
Are you going to shoot him
because this man is evil?

35:56.520 --> 35:57.960
I need men who can fight.

35:59.040 --> 36:02.840
Mosley uses men from Glasgow.

36:02.960 --> 36:07.040
So if the men causing the trouble
are Jewish it will be...explicable.

36:07.160 --> 36:09.800
Since when did you need explanations,
Tommy?

36:09.920 --> 36:11.800
Since I entered politics.

36:11.920 --> 36:13.480
Oh, that's right, yeah.

36:13.600 --> 36:16.680
Oh, yeah.
And how has that been for you, Tom?

36:17.960 --> 36:19.960
Gangs, wars, truces...

36:20.080 --> 36:22.040
Nothing I didn't already know.

36:22.160 --> 36:24.520
(SNORES)

36:26.920 --> 36:32.000
So you think if you kill him, you...
you will kill the message, yeah?

36:33.520 --> 36:35.640
I will kill the man,

36:35.760 --> 36:37.520
then I will kill the message.

36:41.240 --> 36:42.600
How much you paying?

36:43.960 --> 36:45.440
I thought you might do it for the cause,
Alfie.

36:45.560 --> 36:46.560
Fuck off.

36:47.760 --> 36:49.560
Each man will get £20.

36:49.680 --> 36:51.560
You'll get £5,000.

36:51.680 --> 36:53.240
You know, as a god, Tommy, right,

36:53.360 --> 36:59.040
I am now able to just rise above
those kinds of insults, mate.

36:59.160 --> 37:00.680
Ten?

37:03.920 --> 37:05.160
How is my dog?

37:06.680 --> 37:07.760
Your dog is fine.

37:10.400 --> 37:12.320
In that case, ten should be enough.

37:12.440 --> 37:13.560
Where do you want the men?

37:13.680 --> 37:14.600
Birmingham.

37:14.720 --> 37:15.800
No. No.

37:15.920 --> 37:17.680
20 will not be enough

37:17.800 --> 37:20.200
for my lads to step inside
that fucking shit-hole.

37:20.320 --> 37:23.160
It will have to be 25 at least.

37:24.240 --> 37:26.880
25 it is.
You can take your dog back, then, eh?

37:27.000 --> 37:29.480
No, it's better for him
to think that I am still dead.

37:30.800 --> 37:33.080
As it is also with the police.

37:36.960 --> 37:38.200
Right.

37:38.320 --> 37:40.200
So you're still at it, eh, Tommy?

37:40.320 --> 37:42.120
Hmm.

37:42.240 --> 37:44.200
You ain't got no Margate to go to.

37:44.320 --> 37:46.480
(CLICKS TONGUE)

37:46.600 --> 37:47.960
No.

37:50.040 --> 37:52.160
And I have no interest
in shooting seagulls.

37:52.280 --> 37:55.120
Oh, you have
in shooting Cabinet ministers?

37:55.240 --> 37:56.240
Yeah.

37:57.440 --> 37:58.840
And their paid informants.

37:58.960 --> 38:00.640
Mm.

38:03.200 --> 38:07.160
I was on a lot of drugs at first, right,
due to the pain, you know,

38:07.280 --> 38:08.760
on account of it...

38:08.880 --> 38:14.400
Well, you know,
being shot in the face by...some cunt.

38:14.520 --> 38:17.400
I won't bore you with the details
of the trivia.

38:17.520 --> 38:20.760
Nonetheless, I had a recurring dream.

38:22.360 --> 38:26.080
I saw you in a field, right?

38:26.200 --> 38:27.600
With a big black horse.

38:27.720 --> 38:32.640
And you said goodbye, and then...bang.

38:42.160 --> 38:46.120
All right, then. Well, what now?

38:51.840 --> 38:53.480
(SIGHS)

38:59.680 --> 39:00.680
I will continue...

39:03.240 --> 39:06.840
...till I find a man that I can't defeat.

39:10.440 --> 39:11.800
Hmm.

39:37.800 --> 39:40.040
POLLY: Arthur asked whose side I was on.

39:42.040 --> 39:43.880
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

39:55.840 --> 39:57.240
There will be a war.

39:58.640 --> 39:59.960
And one of you will die.

40:01.360 --> 40:03.800
But which one, I cannot tell.

40:05.280 --> 40:06.920
Hmm.

40:09.480 --> 40:10.640
He's gonna do it anyway.

40:11.800 --> 40:15.680
- Yeah.
- You should know,

40:15.800 --> 40:18.480
if Aberama takes his side,
I will kill him.

40:22.000 --> 40:23.280
What about me?

40:27.120 --> 40:29.240
I'll do what I have to do, Pol.

40:31.000 --> 40:33.760
Kill...and kill.

40:35.360 --> 40:37.440
It's the only way to make people listen.

40:50.040 --> 40:52.360
Soon you'll have a stage to stand on.

40:54.400 --> 40:57.440
Millions of people will listen to you.

40:59.240 --> 41:04.640
And you will run the country
like you run this family.

41:04.760 --> 41:06.880
It appears to be what people want.

41:08.320 --> 41:09.320
But not me.

41:10.840 --> 41:12.600
Not any more.

41:12.720 --> 41:14.600
My resignation.

41:23.840 --> 41:24.960
(DOOR OPENS)

41:26.560 --> 41:27.720
(DOOR CLOSES)

41:38.840 --> 41:40.160
(SIGHS)

41:59.920 --> 42:02.040
(PHONE RINGS)

42:20.200 --> 42:23.320
(PHONE RINGS)

42:27.640 --> 42:29.240
(RINGING TONE)

42:32.880 --> 42:36.320
(PHONE RINGS)

42:41.040 --> 42:43.520
(RINGING TONE)

42:58.400 --> 43:01.000
If it's Barney you're worried about,
he's sleeping.

43:01.120 --> 43:03.480
But I can't sleep
because my fucking leg is cracked.

43:13.200 --> 43:15.400
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

43:20.680 --> 43:23.960
- Tell me how my mother went, Charlie.
- (CLEARS THROAT)

43:27.680 --> 43:29.440
You know.

43:29.560 --> 43:30.880
She drowned.

43:33.360 --> 43:35.600
I know it wasn't by accident.

43:39.720 --> 43:40.920
(SIGHS)

43:44.440 --> 43:46.000
Tell me the truth, Charlie.

43:46.120 --> 43:47.840
The truth, Tommy, yeah?

43:47.960 --> 43:49.520
The fucking truth.

43:55.480 --> 43:56.520
Fuck's sake.

44:07.800 --> 44:09.560
She just stepped into the canal.

44:13.240 --> 44:14.720
Your dad was no use.

44:15.840 --> 44:17.840
It was me trying to stop her,
for three days.

44:20.120 --> 44:22.400
In the end, she did it anyway.

44:27.240 --> 44:30.440
- Did she say why?
- Nothing that made sense.

44:32.560 --> 44:34.760
Tell me the things
that didn't make sense.

44:37.320 --> 44:41.040
She said it were the Gypsies
made the nails for Jesus's cross.

44:41.160 --> 44:42.920
That's why we're cursed and restless.

44:45.120 --> 44:47.200
Yeah, go on.

44:47.320 --> 44:49.920
You have to move around
or the guilt catches up with you.

44:52.640 --> 44:55.080
I said,
"Well, why not go on the road for a bit?"

45:02.040 --> 45:03.560
She went to Worcester.

45:04.720 --> 45:06.280
She came back with a white pony.

45:12.640 --> 45:13.840
That one she gave to you.

45:17.200 --> 45:19.520
You used to ride it round, remember?

45:24.280 --> 45:26.720
Well, she seemed happy for a bit,
watching you ride it.

45:30.560 --> 45:31.800
And then she was gone.

45:35.040 --> 45:37.000
None of it made any sense.

45:38.960 --> 45:42.480
Afterwards, whenever I looked
at that white pony, I saw her.

45:48.400 --> 45:50.480
You see, I was in love with her, Tom.

45:53.120 --> 45:54.560
No-one knew but me.

45:57.160 --> 45:59.640
Broke my fucking heart
to pull her from the cut.

46:05.640 --> 46:08.840
You know, your grandfather,
he went the same way.

46:08.960 --> 46:10.920
Suicide.

46:11.040 --> 46:13.200
Sometimes, these things run in the family.

46:16.000 --> 46:18.080
Fuck family, Tom.

46:18.200 --> 46:20.960
You just have to get on with it.

46:21.080 --> 46:22.200
You're a Gypsy.

46:22.320 --> 46:24.560
You have to move around,
or it all catches up with you.

47:10.000 --> 47:13.280
Didn't need all them tablets,

47:13.400 --> 47:16.840
just needed another fucking war, eh?

47:45.240 --> 47:46.160
Perish Judah.

47:46.280 --> 47:47.680
ALL: Perish Judah.

47:55.280 --> 47:58.800
Shalom, my friends. Shalom.

47:58.920 --> 48:00.560
Shalom. Shalom.

48:02.800 --> 48:04.240
In you go, buddy.

48:23.440 --> 48:26.600
Show these fascist bastards no mercy,
brothers.

48:29.240 --> 48:32.000
The Jew and the Gypsy united. (CHUCKLES)

48:32.120 --> 48:34.480
Look, I have got to go, yeah?
I have to go.

48:34.600 --> 48:35.840
Go where?

48:35.960 --> 48:37.640
They're shooting a fascist tonight.

48:37.760 --> 48:39.040
You're gonna do what?

48:39.160 --> 48:40.320
Ssh.

48:41.680 --> 48:43.800
Mosley's in town.

48:43.920 --> 48:45.280
Really?

48:45.400 --> 48:48.160
Look, go into town,

48:48.280 --> 48:50.280
get some drink and some girl

48:50.400 --> 48:52.600
and listen to the radio.

49:04.320 --> 49:08.480
We will not stand by and let this scum
have free rein in our city!

49:08.600 --> 49:13.120
Fascism must not be allowed to voice
its creed of hatred.

49:16.520 --> 49:19.600
- (ANGRY SHOUTING)
- (POLICE WHISTLE BLOWS)

49:19.720 --> 49:21.640
Out the fucking way!

49:23.080 --> 49:25.880
We have a right to protest!

49:26.000 --> 49:27.280
Get back!

49:27.400 --> 49:30.440
Anybody heckles you,
beat the fuck out of them.

49:30.560 --> 49:32.480
(PATRIOTIC MUSIC PLAYS)

49:58.920 --> 50:00.920
We have a right to protest!

50:01.040 --> 50:03.120
We got another one. Let's go. Get, get!

50:03.240 --> 50:04.440
Calm yourself down.

50:05.880 --> 50:07.840
It's not against the law to protest.

50:10.000 --> 50:12.960
THOMAS: Out of the way.
Out of the way. Out of the way.

50:13.080 --> 50:14.000
Let her go.

50:14.120 --> 50:15.960
- I don't need the help of a fascist.
- Yes, you do.

50:16.080 --> 50:19.080
At Steelhouse Lane,
they'll do whatever they want to you.

50:19.200 --> 50:20.200
Let her go.

50:21.360 --> 50:24.560
I'm Tommy Shelby, and I'm ordering you
to let her fucking go. Go on.

50:26.320 --> 50:27.480
Fuck you.

50:27.600 --> 50:31.600
Jessie, you can do more damage
from the inside.

50:31.720 --> 50:33.720
Do you understand?

50:33.840 --> 50:36.400
You can do more damage from the inside.

50:37.560 --> 50:39.240
Come on.

50:39.360 --> 50:40.480
Come on.

50:40.600 --> 50:43.400
Out of the way. Out of the way.

50:43.520 --> 50:44.960
Shut up!

50:46.320 --> 50:48.080
- (FANFARE)
- Here, look.

50:48.200 --> 50:49.840
There, look.

50:49.960 --> 50:51.720
(SNORTS)

50:53.840 --> 50:55.440
I'll join you. (SNORTS)

50:56.640 --> 50:58.080
Play high.

50:58.200 --> 50:59.680
Now, you know what you're doing,
don't you?

50:59.800 --> 51:01.960
Yeah. Tommy checks his pocket watch,

51:02.080 --> 51:03.120
I count ten,

51:03.240 --> 51:04.880
then I blow the other bloke's head off.

51:05.000 --> 51:06.600
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

51:06.720 --> 51:08.000
There, that's for after.

51:08.120 --> 51:10.280
Thank you. Thank you.

51:10.400 --> 51:12.240
- See you later, Arthur.
- Oh, soldier.

51:12.360 --> 51:16.000
Soldier, you do that, you run like fuck.

51:16.120 --> 51:17.840
- Don't stop.
- Run like fuck.

51:17.960 --> 51:19.840
- Yeah.
- Run like fuck.

51:31.560 --> 51:33.080
In here.

51:37.040 --> 51:38.400
Here, for your face.

51:38.520 --> 51:40.200
At least I have only one face.

51:40.320 --> 51:43.200
What did you mean,
"damage from the inside"?

51:43.320 --> 51:44.640
I have a strategy.

51:44.760 --> 51:46.320
You always have a strategy.

51:46.440 --> 51:47.400
But it's dangerous,

51:47.520 --> 51:49.960
and it can't be shared
without sharing the danger.

51:50.080 --> 51:51.360
You think I'm afraid?

51:51.480 --> 51:54.880
No, but it's only gonna put you
in more danger.

51:55.000 --> 51:58.120
Jessie, before the speeches start,
just go home.

51:58.240 --> 51:59.880
There's gonna be lots of arrests.

52:00.000 --> 52:01.240
You have a mark against your name.

52:01.360 --> 52:03.000
Why?

52:03.120 --> 52:04.320
What's going to happen?

52:09.600 --> 52:10.640
I'm gonna do a good thing.

52:12.600 --> 52:14.360
Whenever I do a good thing,

52:14.480 --> 52:16.520
innocent people get hurt.

52:16.640 --> 52:17.680
So go home.

52:18.960 --> 52:22.240
After this evening, we can meet,
discuss strategy.

52:22.360 --> 52:25.560
That beast out there, he's just a beast.

52:25.680 --> 52:27.480
It's like a horse.

52:27.600 --> 52:30.520
It's the rider that decides
what direction it takes.

52:32.640 --> 52:33.880
And who will be the rider?

52:35.280 --> 52:36.520
Just go home.

52:46.200 --> 52:47.320
MOSLEY: Full?

52:47.440 --> 52:49.200
To the fucking brim.

52:50.680 --> 52:51.600
Trouble?

52:51.720 --> 52:53.440
So far, a few communists.

52:54.600 --> 52:57.200
Butlers helped our boys clear them away.

52:57.320 --> 53:00.080
Well, a few hecklers are a good thing.

53:00.200 --> 53:02.600
We can illustrate
how we deal with opposition.

53:02.720 --> 53:06.440
There is a rumour a gang of Jews
are coming up from Digbeth.

53:06.560 --> 53:08.120
No sign of them yet.

53:08.240 --> 53:09.840
Well, let them come.

53:09.960 --> 53:11.560
Welcome them appropriately.

53:14.880 --> 53:16.880
There are a few Peaky boys around.

53:19.120 --> 53:20.360
They are your allies.

53:20.480 --> 53:22.600
There'll be no rifts between us.

53:22.720 --> 53:24.440
Keep your powder dry.

53:30.480 --> 53:32.280
Mr McCavern?

53:34.560 --> 53:36.640
Perish Judah.

53:36.760 --> 53:40.880
- (CHUCKLES)
- No joke, Mr McCavern.

53:44.960 --> 53:45.960
Perish Judah.

53:55.520 --> 54:00.560
- (PATRIOTIC MUSIC PLAYS)
- (APPLAUSE)

54:46.720 --> 54:50.560
You turn the radio on
and turn up the volume.

54:50.680 --> 54:52.400
I want to listen to the news.

54:55.280 --> 54:57.440
(ON RADIO) <i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

54:57.560 --> 54:59.920
Mr Oswald Mosley.

55:00.040 --> 55:01.480
(APPLAUSE)

55:32.720 --> 55:33.880
CROWD: Perish Judah!

55:34.000 --> 55:39.000
Perish Judah! Perish Judah!
Perish Judah! Perish Judah!

55:39.120 --> 55:41.960
Perish Judah! Perish Judah!

55:42.080 --> 55:45.560
Perish Judah! Perish Judah! Perish Judah!

55:45.680 --> 55:51.160
Perish Judah! Perish Judah!
Perish Judah! Perish Judah!

55:51.280 --> 55:53.960
Perish Judah! Perish Judah!

55:54.080 --> 55:59.480
Perish Judah! Perish Judah!
Perish Judah! Perish Judah!

55:59.600 --> 56:02.640
Perish Judah! Perish Judah!

56:02.760 --> 56:04.360
Perish Judah!

56:06.600 --> 56:09.680
- (TAPPING)
- (MICROPHONE FEEDBACK)

56:09.800 --> 56:13.320
Welcome, men and women
of Birmingham.

56:13.440 --> 56:17.280
Thank you for coming here
on this cold, dark night,

56:17.400 --> 56:21.080
in spite of the obstruction
and provocation of our enemies.

56:22.160 --> 56:26.480
Our enemies deal in bricks and stones

56:26.600 --> 56:31.480
and bottles. We deal in reasoned
principle, argument and fact.

56:31.600 --> 56:32.600
(APPLAUSE)

56:32.720 --> 56:37.280
Among those enemies,
we can number Mr Winston Churchill,

56:37.400 --> 56:42.480
who last night condemned me
in the House as a threat to democracy.

56:42.600 --> 56:45.440
(BOOING)

56:49.320 --> 56:51.280
Them's that gone are the lucky ones.

56:51.400 --> 56:52.800
Them's that gone are the lucky ones.

56:56.880 --> 57:01.520
But then Mr Churchill has never been
a friend of the common people.

57:01.640 --> 57:03.880
Faced with the alternative

57:04.000 --> 57:06.480
<i>of saying goodbye to the gold standard,</i>

57:06.600 --> 57:09.080
<i>and therefore to his own employment,</i>

57:09.200 --> 57:12.360
<i>he characteristically selected the latter,</i>

57:12.480 --> 57:13.960
<i>but of course...</i>

57:14.080 --> 57:16.760
<i>...not all attending tonight</i>

57:16.880 --> 57:18.880
<i>will be convinced of our cause.</i>

57:19.000 --> 57:23.600
<i>Some will have come here tonight
to find out for themselves</i>

57:23.720 --> 57:25.840
<i>what we stand for.</i>

57:25.960 --> 57:28.640
Whenever you're ready, Tom.

57:28.760 --> 57:31.720
So here are our guiding principles.

57:31.840 --> 57:35.760
Every citizen shall serve the state.

57:35.880 --> 57:39.360
Not the banks, not factions,

57:39.480 --> 57:41.760
not the Jews!

57:43.280 --> 57:48.280
CROWD: Perish Judah! Perish Judah!
Perish Judah! Perish Judah!

57:49.360 --> 57:52.040
The barriers of class will be abolished

57:52.160 --> 57:53.920
and a greater Britain will be born

57:54.040 --> 57:57.920
of the national socialist
and fascist creed.

57:58.040 --> 57:59.360
(RAPTUROUS APPLAUSE)

58:09.720 --> 58:14.480
It is useless to hide from ourselves
the fact that ever since 1918,

58:14.600 --> 58:17.000
when our heroes returned from France,

58:17.120 --> 58:21.920
our empire has shown all the signs
of disintegration,

58:22.040 --> 58:26.440
and our people are threatened
by gathering disaster.

58:38.440 --> 58:41.440
Get out of my way!

58:41.560 --> 58:42.800
Out of the way!

58:52.760 --> 58:54.280
Go. Go.

59:08.920 --> 59:11.280
(STEADY BREATHING)

59:11.400 --> 59:13.680
(STOPWATCH TICKS)

59:15.080 --> 59:16.960
Ten.

59:17.080 --> 59:19.400
Nine.

59:21.440 --> 59:23.160
Eight.

59:25.000 --> 59:26.720
Seven.

59:27.760 --> 59:29.520
Six.

59:31.960 --> 59:34.600
Five.

59:34.720 --> 59:36.880
Four.

59:37.000 --> 59:38.640
Three.

59:38.760 --> 59:40.280
Two apple crumble...

1:00:07.640 --> 1:00:10.040
(MUFFLED SCREAMS)

1:00:37.080 --> 1:00:39.600
(ANGRY SHOUTING)

1:00:53.320 --> 1:00:56.080
I think it's about time
we got off the stage, old man,

1:00:56.200 --> 1:00:57.880
until this thing is sorted.

1:01:04.960 --> 1:01:08.480
The coppers are here, Arthur.
You gotta get away from the body.

1:01:23.280 --> 1:01:26.520
(STEADY BREATHING)

1:01:32.600 --> 1:01:34.080
What the fuck are you doing here?

1:01:34.200 --> 1:01:35.240
What happened?

1:01:35.360 --> 1:01:36.680
I don't know what happened.

1:01:36.800 --> 1:01:39.880
I don't know what fucking happened.
It doesn't make any fucking sense.

1:01:40.000 --> 1:01:42.480
- (DOOR OPENS)
- Wait. Fuck, it's us.

1:01:44.200 --> 1:01:47.520
Aberama's dead, he's gone.

1:01:47.640 --> 1:01:49.760
He's gone, and they came for me, too.

1:01:50.840 --> 1:01:53.360
What the fuck is she doing here?

1:01:53.480 --> 1:01:55.200
Arthur, they got to Barney.

1:01:55.320 --> 1:01:56.680
They knew everything.

1:01:56.800 --> 1:01:58.480
They knew fucking everything.

1:01:58.600 --> 1:02:00.800
Who? Who knew, Tom?

1:02:00.920 --> 1:02:02.360
Johnny, get this woman out of here.

1:02:02.480 --> 1:02:03.600
- I want to know.
- Yeah.

1:02:03.720 --> 1:02:05.720
Get her out of here. Get her out!

1:02:13.280 --> 1:02:14.760
Doesn't make sense.

1:02:16.600 --> 1:02:18.040
Doesn't make fucking sense.

1:02:19.080 --> 1:02:20.960
Who? Who? Who?

1:02:21.080 --> 1:02:24.440
The Chinese, the Italians...

1:02:26.120 --> 1:02:29.600
...the Branch, Intelligence,
McCavern, Mosley...

1:02:29.720 --> 1:02:32.320
Mosley knew nothing!

1:02:32.440 --> 1:02:33.520
He knew nothing!

1:02:34.920 --> 1:02:36.640
(GLASS SHATTERS)

1:02:39.080 --> 1:02:40.760
(SHOUTS) Who?!

1:02:40.880 --> 1:02:42.600
Jesus fucking Christ.

1:02:42.720 --> 1:02:45.400
You're fucking frightening me, Tom.

1:02:45.520 --> 1:02:46.800
Doesn't make sense.

1:02:50.080 --> 1:02:51.440
Who?

1:02:52.520 --> 1:02:54.880
Who? Who?

1:02:55.000 --> 1:02:56.840
Who?

1:02:56.960 --> 1:02:59.600
ARTHUR: Who? You know, Tom, you must know.

1:03:00.800 --> 1:03:04.360
You're fucking scaring me,
what are you doing?

1:03:07.720 --> 1:03:09.760
Talk to me.

1:03:09.880 --> 1:03:14.320
Maybe I've found him, Arthur,
the man I can't defeat.

1:03:18.120 --> 1:03:20.040
- Mosley?
- I don't know.

1:03:20.160 --> 1:03:21.320
I don't fucking know.

1:03:23.080 --> 1:03:24.400
Doesn't make sense.

1:03:29.280 --> 1:03:30.280
Let's...

1:03:31.560 --> 1:03:32.760
Let's go inside.

1:03:34.520 --> 1:03:35.760
We'll work it out...

1:03:36.840 --> 1:03:38.840
- ...have a drink.
- I need to walk.

1:03:43.480 --> 1:03:46.440
(STEADY BREATHING)

1:04:07.040 --> 1:04:09.480
(BREATHING CONTINUES)

1:04:22.920 --> 1:04:24.880
The work is all done, Tommy.

1:04:25.000 --> 1:04:26.680
It's all done.

1:04:26.800 --> 1:04:29.800
We can walk away from all of this.

1:04:29.920 --> 1:04:31.520
It's so easy.

1:04:31.640 --> 1:04:33.360
It's so soft.

1:04:33.480 --> 1:04:35.440
Such a small change.

1:04:38.200 --> 1:04:40.040
(SCREAMS)
